info.senderName: NWS GreenBay (East Central Wisconsin - Green Bay)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued March 24 at 10:48AM CDT until March 25 at 1:00PM CDT by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Wisconsin... Yellow River at Babcock affecting Wood County. For the Yellow River...including Babcock...Minor flooding is forecast. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL EARLY TOMORROW AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Yellow River at Babcock. * WHEN...Until early Friday afternoon. * IMPACTS...At 12.0 feet, flooding is confined mainly to agricultural...wooded lowland and marshes. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 10:00 AM CDT Thursday the stage was 12.3 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 10:00 AM CDT Thursday was 12.4 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to rise to a crest of 12.4 feet this afternoon. It will then fall below flood stage this evening. - Flood stage is 12.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov/grb The next statement will be issued this evening at 1000 PM CDT.
